Actually, your code is fine, but is missing something. Your transition is not working because you did not specify a transition. 

You should make a trans:hover, trans:clicked or any other state you want, with a css attribute in it, like background-color: red; Then when you hover, click or whatever, you&#39;ll see your transition working just fine. However, your document.write is bad practice. It can fuck things up. 

Try this:

HTML

    &lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
    &lt;html&gt;
        &lt;head&gt;
            &lt;script type=&quot;text/javascript&quot; src=&quot;menu.js&quot;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
            &lt;link rel=&quot;stylesheet&quot; href=&quot;style.css&quot; /&gt;
        &lt;/head&gt;
        &lt;body&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;trans&quot;&gt;aaa&lt;/div&gt;
            &lt;div id=&quot;abc&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/body&gt;
    &lt;/html&gt;


CSS

    .trans {
        text-align: center;
        padding-top: 250px;
        transition: 1s;
        -moz-transition: 5s;
        -ms-transition: 5s;
        -o-transition: 5s;
        -webkit-transition: 5s;
    }    

    .trans:hover {
      background-color: red;
    }


Scripts

    document.getElementById(&quot;abc&quot;).innerHTML = &quot;menu&quot;;

Try it out: https://jsfiddle.net/jlanssie/Ljhawtqx/5/

`document.write(str)` will overwrite tour document so `&lt;div class=&quot;abc&quot;&gt;menu&lt;/div&gt;` will *replace* `&lt;div class=&quot;trans&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;` and that causes your *entire* CSS not to work, *not just transitions*. Use `innerHTML` instead. 



&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-js --&gt;

    let container = document.querySelector(&#39;.trans&#39;);
    let str = `
    &lt;div class=&quot;abc&quot;&gt;menu&lt;/div&gt;
    `;
    container.innerHTML = str;

&lt;!-- language: lang-css --&gt;

    .trans {
        text-align: center;
        padding-top: 250px;
        transition: all 1s ease;
        -moz-transition: all 1s ease;
        -ms-transition: all 1s ease;
        -o-transition: all 1s ease;
        -webkit-transition: all 1s ease;
    }


    .trans:hover {
      background-color: #c00;
      color: white;
    }

&lt;!-- language: lang-html --&gt;

    &lt;div class=&quot;trans&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;!-- end snippet --&gt;

For transitions the syntax is:

    transition: [transition-property] [transition-duration] [transition-timing-function] [transition-delay];

Also remember not all css properties support transitions.

